# Render static-site redirects — bounce share-link traffic over to
# the Go API service.
#
# Render Static Sites' _redirects file supports status 301/302
# redirects to ANY URL (including cross-origin), but status 200
# rewrites (transparent proxy) ONLY work for same-origin targets.
# Since the API lives on a separate .onrender.com subdomain, we
# can't proxy invisibly — we have to redirect.
#
# What that means for users:
#   - Tapping /m/<short> on iMessage 302s to the API, which then
#     302s back to the SPA's long matchup URL. Two-hop, ~200ms.
#     The browser briefly shows matchup-vhl6.onrender.com in the
#     address bar, then settles on matchup-uud5.onrender.com.
#   - Image fetches by crawlers (iMessage / Slack / X) follow
#     302s transparently. The preview image comes out correct.
#
# ConnectRPC POSTs don't need rewrites — services/api.js sets
# API_BASE_URL = https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com when running on
# .onrender.com, so the SPA hits the API directly. CORS is open
# on the API side (AllowedOrigins: ["*"]).

# --- Short-URL share gateway ---
/m/*    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/m/:splat    302
/b/*    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/b/:splat    302

# --- Dynamic OG image renderers ---
# These are what iMessage / Slack / X fetch when they see an
# <meta og:image> tag. The OG HTML the API serves has og:image
# URLs pointing back at the API domain (via PUBLIC_ORIGIN env),
# so in practice this redirect only fires when something pastes
# /og/m/<short>.png directly. Cheap to keep for safety.
/og/*    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/og/:splat    302

# --- Apple App Site Association + Android Asset Links ---
# These files have to live at the app's primary domain. The API
# serves them from env-backed templates; 302 is fine here because
# the OS verifier follows redirects.
/.well-known/*    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/.well-known/:splat    302

# --- SSE event streams ---
# Long-lived GET connections. EventSource follows 302s on the
# initial handshake.
/users/me/activity/events    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/users/me/activity/events    302
/brackets/:id/events         https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/brackets/:id/events         302

# --- Health + share landing beacon ---
# Internal-ish endpoints; OK with redirect.
/health          https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/health          302
/share/landed    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/share/landed    302

# --- SPA fallback (must stay LAST) ---
# Every other path is a React Router route — serve index.html and
# let the SPA handle it client-side. Status 200 (rewrite) here is
# fine because /index.html is same-origin.
/*    /index.html    200
